<promed@promedmail.org>

[Data by country, area, or territory for 21 Sep 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20SEPT21_1632339850.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 11.3% of daily case numbers and 15.0% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 88.20 million cases. Brazil reported over 9000 cases in the last 24 hours, followed by Cuba, while many countries, including the USA, Canada, Guatemala, and Honduras, among others, did not report any cases; 3 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, while 5 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 43.2% of daily case numbers and 40.0% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 68.56 million cases. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Spain, Belgium, Sweden, Switzerland, and Kazakhstan, among others; 17 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, and an additional 7 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 11.2% of daily case numbers and 13.1% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 15.51 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (17 397) over the last 24 hours, followed by Occupied Palestinian Territory, Iraq, Morocco, Pakistan, Jordan, and Libya. Lebanon reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 2.8% of daily case numbers and 3.7% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 5.92 million cases. Botswana (1536) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by South Africa (1504). Ethiopia and Madagascar reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Cameroon, Gambia, and Benin, among other countries, did not report cases over the last 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 16.7% of daily case numbers and 14.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 7.99 million cases. Philippines reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 18 000 cases), followed by Malaysia, Viet Nam, Mongolia, Japan, South Korea, Australia, and Cambodia.

- The South East Asia region reported 11.2% of the daily newly reported cases and 13.1% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 42.59 million cases. India is dominant, reporting over 26 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Thailand (10 919), Indonesia (3263), Myanmar (1687), Bangladesh (1562), and Nepal (1036). Sri Lanka and Maldives have not reported any cases for many days.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 21 Sep 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

